{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: collectors -> aggregation/context builder -> summary-generation call payload. A unit test of one parser would miss missing-source wiring bugs. Higher levels were considered and rejected: behavior text is about payload composition (\"content passed\"), not real HTTP/OS behavior (System) and not model output quality (Agentic).","test_description":"Wire the three source clients as in-process fakes returning distinct sentinel fields, run the report pipeline until the summary-generation adapter, and assert the exact request/context passed to that adapter contains all three source sections and sentinel values.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module fault propagation and fallback rendering (source client error -> report assembly continues). Unit is too low because interaction between fetch, error handling, and rendering is the failure boundary. Higher levels rejected: behavior does not require real network outage mechanics (System) or real model judgment quality (Agentic).","test_description":"Use two healthy in-process source fakes and one fake that raises a timeout/connection exception; run report generation and assert output is produced, contains `data unavailable` for only that section, and the process does not abort.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on the generated narrative content quality, i.e., real model decisions about what values to include and how to describe them. Deterministic stubs would hide hallucination/omission errors. Workflow rejected: behavior describes a single generation quality check, not multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Run summary generation against real model calls on fixed input fixtures with known key values; across repeated runs, assert required facts/values are preserved (and no contradictory values introduced) using a strict fact-check rubric/parser.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary includes real external interfaces (source APIs + email transport/inbox delivery). In-process mocks can pass while real delivery fails due SMTP/API/auth/network behavior. Agentic was considered and rejected: behavior text is delivery outcome (\"reaches inbox correctly\"), not summary semantic quality, so model-quality assertions are not required for this behavior.","test_description":"Execute the script end-to-end against real/staging source endpoints and a real test mailbox, then verify the message is received by configured recipients with expected subject/body structure and attached/embedded report content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.74,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This requires real run-to-run persistence and scheduling boundary behavior (failure on one run, retry on later run) plus unreachable delivery infrastructure semantics. Mock-only tests can miss process-boundary/state persistence issues. Workflow rejected: no multi-agentic decision chain is described; this is infrastructure recovery logic.","test_description":"Run the script in a system test harness across two scheduled executions: first with email service intentionally unreachable, assert report is persisted to local fallback file; second with service restored, assert previously saved report is retried/sent and fallback artifact/state is cleared or marked delivered.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.16,"System":0.79,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
